verbose_text: In principle, D is influenced by mortality that is caused by the transportation process but not expressed until after fish are released from the barge (i.e., " delayed " differential mortality), as well as by direct sources of mortality in the estuary and ocean that are not associated with delayed effects of transportation but have differential effect on transported and in-river migrant fish (see below).
